      "description": "<h3><a name=\"What%27shappening\"></a>What's happening</h3>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>The handoff to a remote A2A agent was configured with <tt>ASYNC: true</tt> in the DSL, but the actual outbound call still went as <tt>async: false</tt>. The trace confirms a blocking sync call was made, not an async push call.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>The platform does not consult the remote agent's <tt>agent-card.json</tt> capabilities (<tt>streaming</tt>, <tt>pushNotifications</tt>) when deciding which mode to use. The decision is based purely on the DSL flag and ignores what the remote agent has declared it supports.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>As a result:\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Streaming mode is never reached, even when the remote agent declares <tt>streaming: true</tt>.</li>\n\t\t<li>Async push mode is not reliably triggered, even when DSL says <tt>ASYNC: true</tt> and the remote agent declares <tt>pushNotifications: true</tt>.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n<h3><a name=\"Whatshouldhappen\"></a>What should happen</h3>\n\n<p>The mode should be picked based on <b>both</b> the DSL flag and the remote agent's advertised capabilities:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class='table-wrap'>\n<table class='confluenceTable'><tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class='confluenceTh'>DSL <tt>ASYNC</tt></th>\n<th class='confluenceTh'>Remote <tt>streaming</tt></th>\n<th class='confluenceTh'>Remote <tt>pushNotifications</tt></th>\n<th class='confluenceTh'>Mode</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>false</tt> (or absent)</td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>false</tt></td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'>any</td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><b>Sync</b></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>false</tt> (or absent)</td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>true</tt></td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'>any</td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><b>Streaming</b></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>true</tt></td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'>any</td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>true</tt></td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><b>Async push</b></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>true</tt></td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'>any</td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><tt>false</tt></td>\n<td class='confluenceTd'><b>Error</b> — async requested but agent does not support push notifications</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n</div>\n\n\n<p>Additionally:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The trace should clearly show which mode was chosen and why.</li>\n\t<li>When a mismatch occurs (e.g., <tt>ASYNC: true</tt> but remote does not support push), the platform should fail fast with a clear error, not silently fall back to sync.</li>\n</ul>\n",
